transcription.text:
Speaker 1: Thank you for calling Viagra. This is Jimmy. How can I help you today?

Speaker 2: Hey, Jimmy. I talked to you last week and you said I told you I was allergic to that stuff and you said you'd send me out something else.

Speaker 1: Uh-huh. Did you get him yet? Well?

Speaker 2: Yeah, but what you sent me was the exact same stuff. I already had it. I was allergic to it.

Speaker 1: No, it's not. Take a look at it.

Speaker 2: Look at the back of the pill. It looks the same. It's going to be a white-shaped diamond pill.

Speaker 1: But it's going to have the number—

Speaker 2: 5-0 on the back.

Speaker 1: Take a look at it. It's not. The label on the bottle said the same.

Speaker 2: The label? Look at the pill. The label is a prescription that you have on file with this.

Speaker 1: But look at the actual pill. The actual pill is not the same pill.

Speaker 2: It has the number 5-0 on the back. The other ones don't have that.

Speaker 1: It's Nick lag. They don't have this. It's made by the same company, which is a five-third labs in France.

Speaker 2: But if you look at the actual pill, it has a number 5-0 on the back. That's how you can tell this is AGV.

Speaker 1: Well, why would the label be the exact same?

Speaker 2: Because that's what your prescription was. That was your original prescription. I changed—

Speaker 1: Thing?

Speaker 2: Prescription to be AGV Viagra. It's still considered Viagra, but it's AGV.

Speaker 1: And that's the one that's the new and improved one. And if you look at it—

Speaker 2: It is. That's the one I ordered. When I read it, my original order was the new one. The AGV is what I ordered.

Speaker 1: The first time? No.

Speaker 2: You got the generic Viagra the first time. That's what you got the first time.

Speaker 1: Did you order online? When you ordered? I'm just curious when you ordered.

Speaker 2: Yeah, yeah. See, that's what—I wish you would have called us then, but that's no problem.

Speaker 1: That's the—you didn't get the AGV. That's the one I sent you with no charge. It's the new and improved AGV.

Speaker 2: That's the different one. So you didn't get that. That's what I'm trying to tell you.

Speaker 1: So it's got a 5-0 on the back?

Speaker 2: Yes, it has a 5-0. It'll be different, the actual pills.

Speaker 1: Yes. Do you have the pills in front of you or not?

Speaker 2: No, I'm driving right now. They're at home.

Speaker 1: I'm just trying to—

Speaker 2: Compare the two. You'll see the difference.

Speaker 1: All right, I'll do that when I get home. I'll give you a call next week if they say.

Speaker 2: Not a problem, but try to—you see the difference when you try it, okay? If it's different.

Speaker 1: But if it's not different, I'm not—

Speaker 2: Again, I don't understand. I get it, but take a look at it.

Speaker 1: Remember, it's the one you won't have the five zero, not the other one. The other one has gonna have some letters.

Speaker 2: This is gonna have the number five. Yeah, okay. All right. I'll check it out. Thanks.
